## Problem
Even with CLI tools, Mode A will not spawn agents unless the skill teaches **when/how** from ambient speech.

## Scope (I005 / B058)
Update `skill/hark/SKILL.md` + `skill/handsfree` + packaged copies under `packages/ultradyn-hark/skills/`.

## Playbook
On `ambient.prompt` intent such as:
- start / spin up / open / launch {claude|codex|grok|cursor|opencode|…}
- new / create herdr session {name}
- start X in {project/path} on {session}
- …and tell it / with prompt {…}

Agent steps:
1. Parse agent, cwd, **Herdr session / space**, kickoff from speech.
2. If **session or space is unclear**, do **not** guess — ask by voice with a
   **brief** suggested options list (configured / running sessions, recent workspaces).
   Same for ambiguous cwd.
3. **One audio question at a time** for the whole flow (session, then cwd, then
   kickoff, etc.). Never stack multiple questions in one TTS turn.
4. Confirm when creating a **new** named session.
5. Run `hark session ensure` / `hark agent-start …` (prefer CLI over raw herdr).
6. TTS short ack with agent + cwd + session + target if known.
7. Do **not** treat spawn as pane delivery; stay outside Herdr as Mode A.
8. File dogfood bugs if herdr start fails mid-voice.

## Acceptance
- [ ] Skill section documents phrases, confirm policy, CLI cheatsheet rows
- [ ] Skill requires clarify (with short option list) when Herdr session/space is ambiguous
- [ ] Skill requires **one audio question at a time** for spawn/setup questions
- [ ] handsfree + npm skill packages stay in sync (same content policy as prior releases)
- [ ] No requirement for library-side NLU (Mode A judgment owns speech parse)